The skins are all labelled with metal tags with the collector’s field number embossed into them (
Figure 4
), while the eggs are labelled with the field number written with pencil directly on their surface (
Figure 5
). One of the eggs (NHMO-BI-92664) is cracked and has previously been attempted to be repaired.
